{
  "text": "Our patient underlines the hypothesis of a common mechanism connecting migraine, CAD and RCVS. The mechanism might involve endothelial dysfunction or impaired vasoreactivity. Patients with migraine, who experience a change in headache phenotype, should be investigated for secondary headaches, especially when red flags for CAD or RCVS are present. [CITATION_1] Careful history taking, clinical information and imaging may help to differentiate between the three types of headache. Early diagnosis is important due to the risk of potential dangerous complications (i.e. intracranial artery dissection with potential subarachnoidal haemorrhage, intracerebral haemorrhage, multiple cerebral infarction due to RCVS, reversible brain oedema, etc.) in untreated secondary headaches.",
